MultiChoice drops Russian news channel, as global sanctions pile up on Moscow DStv subscribers will have access to acclaimed shows including Luca, Cruella, The Mandalorian, The Simpsons and The Kardashians to name a few. MultiChoice, which delivers entertainment services to 21.1 million households across 50 countries on the African continent, believes the Disney deal aligns with the company’s goal of innovation and enhances viewer’s access and entertainment options. “In line with our business objective of adding value and enhancing our ecosystem, we are focused on making sure that all our customers enjoy their favourite shows and movies anywhere, anytime, on our world-class platforms,” says Calvo Mawela, MultiChoice Group CEO. “MultiChoice’s partnership with Disney+ leads with an expanded choice of content, ease and convenience of subscription and payment, with the DStv Explora Ultra as an enabler.” Read:
